cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the problem of human trafficking, which is a major concern in the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed entity resolution pipeline involves techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.DB) to extract clusters of data with prior history of human trafficking activity. The paper also discusses challenges in terms of scalability (cs.SI) and domain-specific characteristics of the resolved entities (cs.SD).
